post_text:
Let us introduce you to HPC's new Music/Band instructor!

My name is Jaeden Beyer. I grew up in Central City, NE and graduated from Central City High School in 2016. I spent the past four years at the University of Nebraska-Lincoln, and just graduated this May! I was involved in various ensembles such as the Cornhusker Marching Band, and the UNL Wind Ensemble. My primary instrument is the flute! I am currently living in Lincoln, and will be moving back to Central City in July! I will be the K-12 Music teacher at HPC. I cannot wait to meet the students and teach them all about music!
text:
Let us introduce you to HPC's new Music/Band instructor!

My name is Jaeden Beyer. I grew up in Central City, NE and graduated from Central City High School in 2016. I spent the past four years at the University of Nebraska-Lincoln, and just graduated this May! I was involved in various ensembles such as the Cornhusker Marching Band, and the UNL Wind Ensemble. My primary instrument is the flute! I am currently living in Lincoln, and will be moving back to Central City in July! I will be the K-12 Music teacher at HPC. I cannot wait to meet the students and teach them all about music!

I just recently moved back to Silver Creek with my fianc√©, Reid and we‚Äôve been working on remodeling our house. In our spare time, we enjoy traveling, fishing, and just spending time with our friends and family. post_text:
Let me introduce HPC Elementary's new Physical Education teacher, Darius!

My name is Darius Williams. I grew up in McCook, NE and graduated from McCook High School in 2015. I attended the University of Nebraska-Kearney where I most recently graduated from in December 2019. I participated as a track athlete while I was at UNK competing in long jump, triple jump, and short sprints. I currently live in Grand Island with my fiance where I moved to after graduation, my fiance is a 2nd grade teacher at Stolley Park Elementary in Grand Island. We are hoping to get married this July so please cross your fingers for us! Some things that my fiance and I like to do are watch any type of Husker athletic, spend time outside, and be with our families. We spend a ton of time out at the lake in the summer. I am very excited to begin my first teaching job at HPC, I will be teaching PK-6 Health & PE as well as coaching varsity football and track. I cannot wait to meet all that are a part of the HPC staff!

post_text:
2020-2021 Kindergarten Class Lists High Plains Community Elementary School is committed to providing your student with an appropriate classroom placement that promotes relationships which lead to the highest potential of learning possible. Teachers spend a great deal of time considering student strengths and learning needs as we create class lists. We also try to form classes that are balanced (gender, social/academic factors, number of students, etc.) If you would like to offer input into your child‚Äôs specific academic or social-emotional needs, please submit your request(s) to Mrs. Beran by email (kberan@hpcstorm.org) by Friday, May 1, 2020. Please do not submit requests for a particular teacher or of particular friends as classmates as these will not be accepted. Parent input is valued; however, parent requests are not guaranteed as many factors come into play in creating classroom groupings. Thank you.

HPC Staff

post_text: Over the weekend, the Governor declared a Directed Health Measure for the counties of Butler, Merrick, Polk, Hall, Hamilton, York, and Seward. Because of this DHM, High Plains Community Schools will extend their closure to May 6th. We truly hope that at some point, HPC will be able to bring students back in order to have some closure to the school year. However, it looks like that opportunity is diminishing. HPC is very proud of its staff, students, and families and the hard work being put in to ensure learning continues. High Plains Community Schools will continue to follow all directed measures from local and state health officials.

post_text: High Plains Community Schools has been approved to provide free sack meals for HPC families who have children ages 1 through 18. Delivery of free sack meals will begin on Tuesday, March 31. Please go to the HPC website to sign up. A link to sign up will be at the bottom left of the page. Sign up by noon each day for next day delivery. Example: Sign up by Monday noon for Tuesday delivery. You may sign up for multiple days during the week. This is an awesome opportunity for HPC to continue to support our great families.

post_text: HPC is proud of our early childhood programs. With 90 percent of brain development occurring before age five, high-quality early child care and education is essential to a child‚Äôs future success. Early learning builds the foundation for skills needed in school, work, and life. Research shows that kids in quality early childhood education programs are more likely to reach developmental milestones early or on time, build emotional intelligence, show improved reading skills, have better math skills in elementary school, and be prepared for kindergarten and to become lifelong learners.
